11/01/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski will pay an official two-day visit to Albania beginning Wednesday (12 January) at the invitation of counterpart Fatos Nano. 
Buckovski will also hold talks with Albanian President Alfred Moisiu and Parliament Speaker Servet Pellumbi, focusing on bilateral and regional issues and the two countries' bids for Euro-Atlantic integration.
In other news, Buckovski has asked all cabinet ministers to present concrete measures and deadlines for implementing reforms. 
He stressed there can be no delay, given the 13 March local elections.
On Monday, meanwhile, parliament member Trifun Kostovski announced he would run for mayor of Skopje against incumbent Risto Penov. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, Vest - 11/01/05)
